SIMPLE: nod
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nod
<hw>Nod</hw> <pr>(n⟦ocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nodden</ets>; cf. OHG. <ets>kn⟦omac⟧t⟦omac⟧n</ets>,
ge<ets>nuot⟦omac⟧n</ets>, to shake, and E. <ets>nudge</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To bend or incline the upper part, with a quick motion;
<as>as, <ex>nodding</ex> plumes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To incline the head with a quick motion; to make a
slight bow; to make a motion of assent, of salutation, or of drowsiness,
with the head; <as>as, to <ex>nod</ex> at one</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be careless or inattentive; to make a mistake
from lack of attention.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor is it Homer <qex>nods</qex>, but we that dream.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To be drowsy or dull; to doze off, especially while
in a sitting position; <as>as, half the class <ex>nodded</ex> while the
professor droned on</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nod</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nod
<hw>Nod</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Nodded</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Nodding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To incline or bend,
as the head or top; to make a motion of assent, of salutation, or of
drowsiness with; <as>as, to <ex>nod</ex> the head</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To signify by a nod; <as>as, to <ex>nod</ex>
approbation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cause to bend.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By every wind that <qex>nods</qex> the mountain pine.</q>
<rj><qau>Keats.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nod</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Nod
<hw>Nod</hw> <pr>(n⟦ocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
dropping or bending forward of the upper part or top of
anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like a drunken sailor on a mast,⟦br⟧
Ready with every <qex>nod</qex> to tumble down.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A quick or slight downward or forward motion of the
head, in assent, in familiar salutation, in drowsiness, or in giving a
signal, or a command; <as>as, a <ex>nod</ex> of approval</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A look or a <qex>nod</qex> only ought to correct them [the
children] when they do amiss.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nations obey my word and wait my <qex>nod</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The land of Nod</b></col>, <cd>sleep.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nodal</ent>⟦br⟧
